		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">WDC（water-based drilling cuttings） were used as a replacement for natural clay to prepare sintered bricks. The water content of the WDC can be reduced from 80% to 20% through press filter pretreatment, which can meet the requirements of external delivery for recycling. The remaining water in the WDC can be used directly to make bricks (240 mm × 115 mm × 53 mm) to reduce the consumption of water resources. The entire production process includes raw material preparation, mixing, pressing, drying and sintering (temperature of 800–1000 °C; time for 1-4 h)</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="6da6f531-a1d0-40f7-a205-2ba2068aee96" uri="../sources/6da6f531-a1d0-40f7-a205-2ba2068aee96.xml">
